   "source": [
    "# Lissajous Figure\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider two simple harmonic motions represented as\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "& y_1 = a_1 \\sin\\theta\\\\\n",
    "& y_2 = a_2 \\sin(\\theta + \\delta)\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "where \n",
    "\n",
    "*    $a_1$, $a_2$ are amplitudes, \n",
    "*    $\\delta$ is the phase difference which can take some fixed values, and \n",
    "*    $\\theta$ is a continuous variable from $0$ to $2\\pi$.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "We want to study the relationship between two motions by plotting $y_2$ against $y_1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "314c2b0f-9f58-4279-a097-278cf2dd4aef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Algorithm for Generating Lissajous Figure\n",
    "\n",
    "## Steps:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Define Function `f(a1, a2, delta)`:**\n",
    "   - Generate 100 values for `theta` in the range $[0, 2\\pi]$.\n",
    "   - Compute `y1` as $ a1 \\cdot \\sin(\\theta) $.\n",
    "   - Compute `y2` as $ a2 \\cdot \\sin(\\theta + \\text{radians}(\\delta)) $.\n",
    "   - Return `y1` and `y2`.\n",
    "\n",
    "2. **Initialize Variables:**\n",
    "   - Set `a1 = 2`, `a2 = 1`, and `delta = 90`.\n",
    "   - Call function `f(a1, a2, delta)` to obtain `y1` and `y2`.\n",
    "\n",
    "3. **Plot Lissajous Figure:**\n",
    "   - Create a figure of size \\(5 \\times 5\\).\n",
    "   - Plot `y1` vs. `y2` using a red dashed line (`'r-'`).\n",
    "   - Set x-axis limits to `[-2, 2]` and y-axis limits to `[-2, 2]`.\n",
    "   - Label axes with `\"$y_1$\"` and `\"$y_2$\"`, using LaTeX-style notation.\n",
    "   - Set title as `\"Lissajous Figure\"`.\n",
    "   - Add grid and legend.\n",
    "   - Display the plot."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "id": "0426f73e-460a-44b8-a061-8c8eabee4caa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "id": "b213acad-20d5-42d2-90d1-49f3b1b5c935",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 500x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def f(a1, a2, delta):\n",
    "    theta = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 100)\n",
    "    y1 = a1 * np.sin(theta)\n",
    "    y2 = a2 * np.sin(theta + np.radians(delta))\n",
    "    return y1, y2\n",
    "\n",
    "a1, a2, delta = 2, 1, 90\n",
    "y1, y2 = f(a1, a2, delta)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize = (5, 5))\n",
    "plt.plot(y1, y2, 'r-', label = f\"$\\\\delta$ = {int(delta)}$^\\\\circ$\")\n",
    "plt.xlim(-2, 2)\n",
    "plt.ylim(-2, 2)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"$y_1$\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"$y_2$\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Lissajous Figure\", fontsize=16)\n",
    "plt.grid()\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  }
